<h1><a id="FLASK_SERVER_SETUP_UBUNTU_1804_0"></a>FLASK SERVER SETUP UBUNTU 18.04</h1>
<h3><a id="Installation_1"></a>Installation</h3>
<p>Install the Components from the Ubuntu Repositories.</p>
<pre><code class="language-sh">$ sudo apt-get update
$ sudo apt-get install python3-pip python3-dev
$ pip3 install virtualenv --user
$ <span class="hljs-built_in">source</span> ~/.bashrc
</code></pre>
<h3><a id="Create_a_Python_Virtual_Environment_10"></a>Create a Python Virtual Environment</h3>
<p>We need to create a virtual environment to store our Flask projectâ€™s Python requirements. After create virtual environment we need to activate:</p>
<pre><code class="language-sh">$ mkdir ~/server
$ <span class="hljs-built_in">cd</span> ~/server
$ virtualenv env 
$ <span class="hljs-built_in">source</span> env/bin/activate
</code></pre>
<h3><a id="Set_Up_a_Flask_Application_19"></a>Set Up a Flask Application</h3>
<pre><code class="language-sh">$ pip install flask
$ nano ~/server/app.py
</code></pre>
<p>Copy and paste the below code:</p>
<pre><code>from flask import Flask
app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route(&quot;/&quot;)
def hello():
    return &quot;&lt;h1 style='color:blue'&gt;It's Work!&lt;/h1&gt;&quot;
if __name__ == &quot;__main__&quot;:
    app.run(host='0.0.0.0')
</code></pre>
<h3><a id="Test_Flask_Application_35"></a>Test Flask Application</h3>
<pre><code class="language-sh">python ~/server/app.py
</code></pre>
<p>If you have UFW firewall enabled we need to open port by: <code>sudo ufw allow 5000</code><br>
Open in your web browser: <code>http://server_domain_or_IP:5000</code></p>
